INFLUENZA (42): USA, MORE EARLY SIGNS PREDICT SEVERE INFLUENZA SEASON
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 15 Dec 2014
From Michael Sauri <msauri@ohcmd.com> [edited]


Reporting influenza vaccine failures and shortages of Tamiflu in local pharmacies suggesting a significant 2014-2015 influenza H3N2 mismatch
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
As our local influenza season starts to ramp up, I would like to report to ProMED-mail members that in the past week, I have seen in my clinic 3 documented cases of influenza A (by quick flu test) in patients previously vaccinated with the current 2014-2015 [seasonal] influenza vaccine.

In addition, last week my office staff reported to me that many local pharmacies have run out of Tamiflu due to increase demand, which suggests that other local physicians are having a similar experience.

Taken together, these findings occurring early in our influenza season suggests that this flu season will be severe due to this season's influenza vaccine mismatch, as well as the tendency for more severe flu seasons when the H3N2 strain predominates.

--
Michael Sauri, MD, FACP, FACPM, FACOEM, FRSTM&H, CTropMed
Medical Director
Occupational Health Consultants
15005 Shady Grove Road, Suite 450
Rockville, Maryland 20850
